commitResults.messageBody: Created a skeletal new chatbot Davvy that greets user and exit

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix typo referring to chatbot name

commitResults.messageBody:
A new method that allows user input to be returned back to the command
line was added to help the user ensure the correct message is being
received

A list that allows the saving of user input allows for multiple saved
inputs that can be retrieved later on when requested by the user

Refactored the code by splitting the adding function of tasks into a
list into a separate class for easier management and future scalability.

Deleted Duke.java as it was useless.

Main changes in the way user input is parsed, this time taking first
word as command and subsequent word as argument.

Moved printing to helper methods for easier overriding when new classes
are implemented with different printing

commitResults.messageTitle: Add todo, event and deadline feature
commitResults.messageBody:
Three new different types of tasks can now be added to the bot, with
new fields for each, such as custom due date and time
